RACE.FOOTNOTES: DAYKRA sped to the lead shortly away from the gate, quickly opened a clear advantage and widened down the lane having never been challenged as much best. LOONY stalked the pacesetter down the backside, could never close the gap on that one but finished willingly to be second best. MONUMENTALJUSTICE tracked the leaders from mid-pack to the turn, split rivals with a mild bid at the quarter pole and finished well. STARLITE RUN rated in mid-pack to the turn, circled up five wide and showed some late interest. MR NEGATIVITY chased the pace from three wide and lacked a closing response. BIG ANCHOR raced near the rear of the field and passed weaker rivals in the stretch. LEA ANN'S PRINCESS slow early to be well behind the pack and picked up ground late never having been a threat. SHOWDOWN JUSTICE showed brief speed to be prominent early and gradually gave way. T. V. VICTORY was never a factor.

MYGALJUSTICE broke alertly to take the lead from the gate crossing the field to the first turn, set a pressured pace from the half mile pole, responded well to all challenges to the head of the lane and weakened coming home. PRESCIENCE pressed the pace down the backside racing from between rivals and faded in the turn. CLEVER KATE trailed most of the way and was never a threat.
